U.S. PRODUCT APPROVALS

 ON

JANUARY 25, 2008, THE FDA APPROVED

EMEND

(FOSAPREPITANT DIMEGLUMINE) FOR INJECTION, 115 MG, FOR THE

PREVENTION OF

CHEMOTHERAPY-INDUCED

NAUSEA AND VOMITING.

